1
00:02:11,865 --> 00:02:12,832
Oh, God!

2
00:02:12,866 --> 00:02:14,731
What?

3
00:02:14,767 --> 00:02:17,031
Didn't you see that?

4
00:02:17,070 --> 00:02:18,037
There was a dead cat...

5
00:02:18,071 --> 00:02:19,663
hanging from that sign
we just passed.

6
00:02:19,706 --> 00:02:21,640
Really? Cool.

7
00:02:23,643 --> 00:02:26,009
Don't you even think
about going back there.

8
00:02:26,045 --> 00:02:28,673
What color was it?

9
00:02:28,715 --> 00:02:29,909
Tiger-striped.

10
00:02:29,949 --> 00:02:31,041
What difference
does it make?

11
00:02:31,084 --> 00:02:33,279
Well, I thought it might
be black, you know?

12
00:02:33,319 --> 00:02:35,150
Satanists out in the desert.

13
00:02:36,356 --> 00:02:40,156
Marielle said the Nevada desert
was full of oddballs.

14
00:02:44,130 --> 00:02:47,031
I just don't know who could kill
a living creature like that.

15
00:02:47,066 --> 00:02:49,193
You're traveling through
another dimension...

16
00:02:49,235 --> 00:02:52,295
A dimension not only
of sight and sound, but of mind.

17
00:02:52,338 --> 00:02:53,737
Very funny.

18
00:02:57,177 --> 00:03:00,203
I can't wait to get back
to Salt Lake City, at least.

19
00:03:00,246 --> 00:03:02,180
Too much nature out here.

20
00:03:02,215 --> 00:03:05,013
I'm starting to miss civilization.

21
00:03:05,051 --> 00:03:06,211
What? What is it?

22
00:03:06,252 --> 00:03:09,688
A car. Really movin', too.

23
00:03:09,722 --> 00:03:12,850
Get over.
Give him the road.

24
00:03:14,827 --> 00:03:16,590
It's a cop.

25
00:03:18,064 --> 00:03:20,658
Why is he going so fast
with his flashers off?

26
00:03:20,700 --> 00:03:23,100
Who's he gonna
run them for out here?

27
00:03:23,136 --> 00:03:25,263
Well, there's us.

28
00:03:29,108 --> 00:03:31,599
What's he doing?

29
00:03:31,644 --> 00:03:33,271
I don't know.

30
00:03:47,560 --> 00:03:49,255
Hi.

31
00:04:08,581 --> 00:04:10,048
What does he want?

32
00:04:10,083 --> 00:04:12,381
Well, I guess he wants
to get back behind us again.

33
00:04:12,418 --> 00:04:14,318
Well, why didn't
he just pull over...

34
00:04:14,354 --> 00:04:15,912
and let us pass then,
if that's what he wants?

35
00:04:15,955 --> 00:04:17,320
I don't know.

36
00:04:25,431 --> 00:04:27,763
Why is he stopping us,
Peter? Why?

37
00:04:27,800 --> 00:04:30,598
These asses have
a quota to make.

38
00:04:30,637 --> 00:04:32,798
They keep the posted limit at 55
so they can make it.

39
00:04:32,839 --> 00:04:33,806
Don't pull over.

40
00:04:33,840 --> 00:04:35,307
I don't have a choice, Mary.

41
00:04:42,615 --> 00:04:43,912
Great.

42
00:04:56,396 --> 00:04:59,331
Holy God, it's Sasquatch!

43
00:05:04,771 --> 00:05:07,171
Guess I was going
a little fast, officer.

44
00:05:07,206 --> 00:05:09,640
Had the hammer
down a little, huh?

45
00:05:13,313 --> 00:05:16,043
Can I see your registration
please, sir?

46
00:05:16,082 --> 00:05:17,674
No problem.

47
00:05:19,052 --> 00:05:21,520
But the car's not mine.

48
00:05:21,554 --> 00:05:22,612
It's my sister's.

49
00:05:22,655 --> 00:05:26,250
We're driving it back
for her to New York.

50
00:05:26,292 --> 00:05:28,988
She's... she goes
to school in Oregon.

51
00:05:29,028 --> 00:05:30,120
Rand College.

52
00:05:30,163 --> 00:05:31,528
Have you ever heard of it?

53
00:05:32,899 --> 00:05:34,491
Mar, could you get
the registration?

54
00:05:34,534 --> 00:05:36,968
I think it's in
the glove compartment.

55
00:05:37,003 --> 00:05:39,528
I don't believe this...

56
00:05:39,572 --> 00:05:41,062
I can't find my license.

57
00:05:42,775 --> 00:05:44,640
Sorry, officer, I...

58
00:05:44,677 --> 00:05:47,407
Oh, wait a minute, here it is.

59
00:05:49,382 --> 00:05:52,317
OK, and, um, here's
the registration.

60
00:05:52,352 --> 00:05:53,478
Oh, good.

61
00:05:53,519 --> 00:05:54,918
I see you're
an organ donor.

62
00:05:56,422 --> 00:05:58,652
Think that's wise?

63
00:05:59,826 --> 00:06:02,351
Well...

64
00:06:10,737 --> 00:06:13,001
Is there a problem, officer?

65
00:06:13,039 --> 00:06:16,475
Your name is Jackson?

66
00:06:16,509 --> 00:06:20,468
The one on the pink slip
says Deirdre Finney.

67
00:06:22,148 --> 00:06:23,342
That your sister?

68
00:06:23,383 --> 00:06:24,680
Right.

69
00:06:24,717 --> 00:06:26,207
She's been divorced
for about a year...

70
00:06:26,252 --> 00:06:28,777
but she kept
her husband's last name.

71
00:06:28,821 --> 00:06:30,721
Deirdre's a bit of a flake.

72
00:06:31,958 --> 00:06:33,482
Bit of a flake, huh?

73
00:06:33,526 --> 00:06:35,084
Tak.

74
00:06:38,398 --> 00:06:41,390
Can I ask you to step
out of the car, Mr. Jackson?

75
00:06:41,434 --> 00:06:42,526
What for?

76
00:06:46,038 --> 00:06:47,596
Of course.

77
00:06:55,281 --> 00:06:57,715
Come around back, Mr. Jackson.

78
00:07:02,789 --> 00:07:04,882
Hell!

79
00:07:04,924 --> 00:07:07,085
Peter, what is it?

80
00:07:07,126 --> 00:07:10,095
Our...
our damn license plate fell off!

81
00:07:10,129 --> 00:07:11,653
I doubt it.

82
00:07:11,697 --> 00:07:14,063
Did you stop in Fallon?

83
00:07:14,100 --> 00:07:17,365
Yeah, we got gas
at the Conoco there.

84
00:07:17,403 --> 00:07:18,802
Why?

85
00:07:18,838 --> 00:07:21,773
They got some
light-fingered kids hang out there.

86
00:07:21,808 --> 00:07:27,110
I reckon your license plate
is hangin' in their clubhouse right now.

87
00:07:27,146 --> 00:07:29,444
You know this and
it still goes on?

88
00:07:29,482 --> 00:07:31,643
Oh, Fallon is not my place.

89
00:07:31,684 --> 00:07:34,915
Those are not my ways.
Gosh, no.

90
00:07:36,222 --> 00:07:39,248
What should
we do about that, officer?

91
00:07:39,292 --> 00:07:41,226
Well, you just take
the plate off the front...

92
00:07:41,260 --> 00:07:42,386
and put it in the back.

93
00:07:42,428 --> 00:07:43,417
That's should get you
across the country.

94
00:07:43,463 --> 00:07:44,760
You got a tool kit?

95
00:07:46,132 --> 00:07:47,759
These are yours.

96
00:07:47,800 --> 00:07:49,233
Thanks.

97
00:07:49,268 --> 00:07:51,259
I think I saw a tool kit
in the trunk.

98
00:07:51,304 --> 00:07:52,828
Yeah, OK.

99
00:08:03,149 --> 00:08:05,674
There, behind
my make-up case.

100
00:08:12,792 --> 00:08:13,884
Hey.

101
00:08:13,926 --> 00:08:16,053
What is this?

102
00:08:19,632 --> 00:08:21,657
Damned sister!

103
00:08:21,701 --> 00:08:23,066
Officer, I know what
this looks like.

104
00:08:24,504 --> 00:08:25,630
But we checked her stuff...

105
00:08:25,671 --> 00:08:26,865
But we're not
customs officers!

106
00:08:26,906 --> 00:08:28,703
That... that is not our dope!

107
00:08:28,741 --> 00:08:29,969
No.

108
00:08:44,390 --> 00:08:46,551
Let me have your keys.

109
00:08:51,998 --> 00:08:54,330
Get in the car.

110
00:08:54,367 --> 00:08:55,629
But...

111
00:08:55,668 --> 00:08:58,728
Are you deaf?
Get in the car!

112
00:08:58,771 --> 00:09:00,898
Get in the car!

113
00:09:03,209 --> 00:09:06,144
OK, we'll get this
taken care of.

114
00:09:06,178 --> 00:09:08,078
In Desperation.

115
00:09:08,114 --> 00:09:10,048
Get in the car, folks.

116
00:09:10,082 --> 00:09:11,379
Tak.

117
00:10:07,039 --> 00:10:09,405
Slow down,
you'll flip us!

118
00:10:20,853 --> 00:10:23,321
What are you doing?
Are you crazy?

119
00:10:31,163 --> 00:10:32,721
Officer, you saw
our registration.

120
00:10:32,765 --> 00:10:35,063
You know that isn't our car,
and it's not our dope either!

121
00:10:35,101 --> 00:10:36,068
Do you think
we'd be so stupid...

122
00:10:36,102 --> 00:10:39,435
Shut up, you
New York deviant.

123
00:10:39,472 --> 00:10:42,635
Wh... wh... what
did you call me?

124
00:10:42,675 --> 00:10:45,508
I'm arresting you
for possession of marijuana...

125
00:10:45,544 --> 00:10:47,535
with intent to sell.

126
00:10:47,580 --> 00:10:49,707
You can't be serious!

127
00:10:49,749 --> 00:10:51,307
You have the right
to remain silent.

128
00:10:51,350 --> 00:10:53,443
If you choose
to not be silent...

129
00:10:53,486 --> 00:10:55,181
everything you say
can be held against you...

130
00:10:55,221 --> 00:10:56,711
In a court of law.

131
00:10:56,756 --> 00:10:57,848
You have the right
to an attorney.

132
00:10:57,890 --> 00:10:59,289
I am going to kill you.

133
00:10:59,325 --> 00:11:01,020
If you cannot
afford an attorney...

134
00:11:01,060 --> 00:11:02,823
One will be
provided for you.

135
00:11:02,862 --> 00:11:03,954
Do you understand
your rights...

136
00:11:03,996 --> 00:11:06,157
as I have explained them
to you?

137
00:11:09,068 --> 00:11:11,468
Do you understand
your rights?

138
00:11:11,504 --> 00:11:13,267
Just... Act normally.

139
00:11:13,305 --> 00:11:15,296
I don't think he understands
what he just said.

140
00:11:15,341 --> 00:11:17,707
Do you understand your rights?!

141
00:11:17,743 --> 00:11:20,211
Do you or not?
Answer me...

142
00:11:20,246 --> 00:11:23,579
you smart-aleck blue state
unisex swingles!

143
00:11:23,616 --> 00:11:27,108
Do you or not?
Do you or not?

144
00:11:27,153 --> 00:11:29,018
Yes! Yes,
we understand.

145
00:11:29,055 --> 00:11:31,046
Please, just watch the road.

146
00:11:35,194 --> 00:11:36,661
Don't worry about me.

147
00:11:36,696 --> 00:11:38,687
I got eyes in the back
of my head.

148
00:11:40,900 --> 00:11:43,528
You'd do well
to remember that.

149
00:11:59,351 --> 00:12:02,184
Up there on the horizon's
the china pit.

150
00:12:03,222 --> 00:12:05,019
Gotta go
all the way to Peru

151
00:12:05,057 --> 00:12:06,490
to find a bigger one.

152
00:12:08,294 --> 00:12:10,558
Yeah, we just started
working her again.

153
00:12:10,596 --> 00:12:13,190
They got some kind
of technology...

154
00:12:13,232 --> 00:12:15,723
that makes even
the tailings valuable.

155
00:12:15,768 --> 00:12:18,328
Science, huh?

156
00:12:18,370 --> 00:12:19,894
Gosh.

157
00:12:21,207 --> 00:12:23,266
Yeah, I think we're gonna
be a boom town again...

158
00:12:23,309 --> 00:12:24,537
just like in the old days.

159
00:13:45,357 --> 00:13:46,881
Officer, please don't kill us.

160
00:13:46,926 --> 00:13:49,793
We'll do whatever you say.
Just don't kill us!

161
00:13:49,829 --> 00:13:52,491
Shut your quackin'
yuppie pothead mouth!

162
00:13:52,531 --> 00:13:54,089
We're not potheads.

163
00:13:54,133 --> 00:13:56,795
You look like potheads to me.

164
00:13:58,604 --> 00:14:00,868
Yuppies killed
Princess Di, you know.

165
00:14:00,906 --> 00:14:02,669
Wasn't she beautiful?

166
00:14:02,708 --> 00:14:03,902
Officer...

167
00:14:03,943 --> 00:14:06,138
Shut up and walk.

168
00:14:06,178 --> 00:14:07,975
Where is everybody?

169
00:14:08,013 --> 00:14:09,571
Disneyland.

170
00:14:09,615 --> 00:14:12,778
Come on, walk,
hay foot, straw foot.

171
00:14:14,653 --> 00:14:16,712
You're Peter.

172
00:14:16,755 --> 00:14:18,780
You're Mary.

173
00:14:18,824 --> 00:14:20,792
So where's Paul?

174
00:14:20,826 --> 00:14:23,454
<i>I mean, how can you sing
Puff the Magic Dragon</i>

175
00:14:23,495 --> 00:14:25,895
without Paul?

176
00:14:27,700 --> 00:14:32,034
Wait a minute.
Peter Jackson.

177
00:14:32,071 --> 00:14:35,268
<i>I love Lord of the Rings!</i>

178
00:14:36,308 --> 00:14:38,776
You are useless.

179
00:14:38,811 --> 00:14:40,870
You at least look healthy.

180
00:14:40,913 --> 00:14:42,574
Get in there, girlfriend.

181
00:14:52,424 --> 00:14:53,789
Forgot all about her.

182
00:14:53,826 --> 00:14:57,227
You can never remember
everything, now can you?

183
00:14:58,564 --> 00:15:02,796
I don't care if you're
a Jew, a Hindu, or Mr. Magoo.

184
00:15:02,835 --> 00:15:04,860
In Desperation...

185
00:15:04,904 --> 00:15:08,738
We don't care about
those things much.

186
00:15:19,618 --> 00:15:22,109
Peter!

187
00:15:22,154 --> 00:15:24,554
Peter! Let me go!

188
00:15:24,590 --> 00:15:26,785
Peter!

189
00:15:30,663 --> 00:15:32,028
Shotgun, get the shotgun!

190
00:15:32,064 --> 00:15:33,053
Shoot him, shoot him!

191
00:15:33,098 --> 00:15:34,998
Get it!
Get it, woman!

192
00:15:35,034 --> 00:15:36,968
Pick it up,
for God sakes!

193
00:15:37,002 --> 00:15:38,094
Don't do that.

194
00:15:50,449 --> 00:15:53,077
Drop it, Mary.

195
00:15:53,118 --> 00:15:54,745
Put it down, Mary.

196
00:15:54,787 --> 00:15:56,516
Put it down.

197
00:15:57,623 --> 00:15:59,250
Drop it.

198
00:16:14,306 --> 00:16:15,295
Now, if you don't
want to see your liver...

199
00:16:15,341 --> 00:16:16,638
come squirting
out of your nose...

200
00:16:16,675 --> 00:16:18,165
I'd put it down, Mary.

201
00:16:32,658 --> 00:16:34,785
Kill me if you're going to.

202
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:42,762
Now, why would
I want to kill you...

203
00:16:42,801 --> 00:16:44,792
when things are
just starting to get interesting?

204
00:16:51,176 --> 00:16:52,609
He killed my husband!

205
00:16:52,644 --> 00:16:54,703
He killed our little girl.

206
00:16:54,747 --> 00:16:57,648
Three billion red Chinese
don't give a damn.

207
00:16:57,683 --> 00:16:59,548
How they hangin', old timer?

208
00:17:07,226 --> 00:17:10,593
Don't you hurt him!
I'm warning you.

209
00:17:10,629 --> 00:17:12,062
Who are you, boy?

210
00:17:12,097 --> 00:17:14,622
I'm David Carver.

211
00:17:14,666 --> 00:17:18,864
I live at 248 Poplar Street
in Wentworth, Ohio.

212
00:17:22,307 --> 00:17:24,537
Yeah, but...

213
00:17:24,576 --> 00:17:26,373
who made thee?

214
00:17:27,679 --> 00:17:30,546
Canst thou say
who made thee? Tak!

215
00:17:32,017 --> 00:17:35,453
I guess my folks did.

216
00:17:35,487 --> 00:17:36,681
And God.

217
00:17:38,557 --> 00:17:42,653
There's no god
out here, little Dave.

218
00:17:42,694 --> 00:17:45,663
Leave him alone!

219
00:17:45,697 --> 00:17:48,029
Haven't you done
enough to our family?

220
00:17:48,067 --> 00:17:50,900
Even bald-headed
hoppin'- Satan...

221
00:17:50,936 --> 00:17:54,770
don't step his split-foot
much west of Tonopah.

222
00:17:54,807 --> 00:17:56,900
This is Desperation.

223
00:17:58,444 --> 00:18:01,436
Only thing out here
is can tah and can tak.

224
00:18:02,714 --> 00:18:04,909
And don't you forget it!

225
00:18:23,602 --> 00:18:24,796
You're mine.

226
00:18:35,581 --> 00:18:37,742
David, what's wrong?

227
00:18:38,851 --> 00:18:40,079
What's... what's
wrong with him?

228
00:18:42,554 --> 00:18:45,079
There's nothing
wrong with him.

229
00:18:45,124 --> 00:18:46,648
What do you mean?
Are you blind?

230
00:18:48,794 --> 00:18:51,922
I think your son
is praying.

231
00:19:27,132 --> 00:19:30,226
Well. Hey there.

232
00:19:30,269 --> 00:19:32,703
Are you a nice person?

233
00:19:34,339 --> 00:19:36,204
Well, I like to think so...

234
00:19:36,241 --> 00:19:38,072
but, then again,
if I was Ted Bundy...

235
00:19:38,110 --> 00:19:39,441
do you think I'd tell you?

236
00:19:39,478 --> 00:19:42,470
I'd know.
I got a psychic streak.

237
00:19:44,550 --> 00:19:46,541
Up yours!

238
00:19:47,619 --> 00:19:50,053
That's pleasant.

239
00:19:50,088 --> 00:19:51,885
So what's your name,
young lady?

240
00:19:51,924 --> 00:19:53,221
Cynthia Smith.

241
00:19:53,258 --> 00:19:56,557
Smith? Oh. Smith.
That's a likely story.

242
00:19:56,595 --> 00:19:58,688
No, really, it is.

243
00:19:58,730 --> 00:19:59,890
Sure.

244
00:19:59,932 --> 00:20:01,092
Honest!

245
00:20:01,133 --> 00:20:02,122
OK.

246
00:20:02,167 --> 00:20:03,566
Who are you?

247
00:20:03,602 --> 00:20:08,471
Me? Steve Ames.
A noble moniker.

248
00:20:08,507 --> 00:20:12,807
So, haul your psychic
streak on up here...

249
00:20:12,844 --> 00:20:13,833
Cynthia Smith...

250
00:20:13,879 --> 00:20:17,110
And let's make
some miles, OK?

251
00:20:17,149 --> 00:20:19,083
Yeah, I guess you'll do.

252
00:20:19,117 --> 00:20:22,848
Oh. Well, thank you
very much, cookie.

253
00:20:22,888 --> 00:20:26,221
Don't call me cookie,
and I won't call you cake.

254
00:20:27,392 --> 00:20:29,724
Oh, my.

255
00:20:36,101 --> 00:20:38,831
You gonna smoke that
or gum it to death?

256
00:20:41,440 --> 00:20:42,702
Yeah, I quit.

257
00:20:42,741 --> 00:20:44,971
Never hurts to keep
in practice, though.

258
00:20:54,820 --> 00:20:57,015
What you lookin' at, huh?

259
00:20:57,055 --> 00:20:58,613
Your T-shirt.

260
00:20:58,657 --> 00:20:59,624
Yeah, right!

261
00:20:59,658 --> 00:21:01,023
I'm lookin' at your t-shirt!

262
00:21:01,059 --> 00:21:03,050
Come on, that's OK!
We're all animals, right?

263
00:21:03,095 --> 00:21:05,563
Oh, come on, now!
Give me a break.

264
00:21:05,597 --> 00:21:10,296
<i>I worked with Dylan back in '95
when, uh, he did Unplugged.</i>

265
00:21:10,335 --> 00:21:11,302
No way!

266
00:21:11,336 --> 00:21:12,394
Yeah, yeah way. Yeah.

267
