529
00:37:11,829 --> 00:37:13,353
Bryan, look out!

530
00:37:20,371 --> 00:37:22,100
Bryan!

531
00:37:22,139 --> 00:37:23,436
Bryan!

532
00:37:31,182 --> 00:37:33,116
Bryan, are you OK?

533
00:37:37,321 --> 00:37:39,152
Bryan, are you...

534
00:37:42,994 --> 00:37:45,019
Help me! Somebody help me!

535
00:37:45,062 --> 00:37:46,620
I think he's dying!

536
00:37:48,499 --> 00:37:50,091
Come on, please.

537
00:37:51,936 --> 00:37:53,801
God, please don't
let him die.

538
00:37:55,906 --> 00:37:58,568
If you save him,
I'll do something for you.

539
00:38:00,177 --> 00:38:02,111
Anything you want,
I promise.

540
00:38:04,315 --> 00:38:06,044
Only don't let him die.

541
00:38:07,151 --> 00:38:08,846
Please don't let him die.

542
00:38:10,288 --> 00:38:12,051
God could work a miracle
on your friend...

543
00:38:12,089 --> 00:38:14,421
but not on your baby sister?

544
00:38:15,926 --> 00:38:17,757
He couldn't save her
from that cop?

545
00:38:19,463 --> 00:38:21,090
What kind of a god is that?

546
00:38:21,132 --> 00:38:23,828
I don't know what kind
of god he is.

547
00:38:23,868 --> 00:38:24,892
Look, leave him alone.

548
00:38:24,935 --> 00:38:26,197
I want to know how you
can get on your knees...

549
00:38:26,237 --> 00:38:28,762
and pray to a god
who killed your sister!

550
00:38:30,841 --> 00:38:32,001
Lady, he's your son...

551
00:38:32,043 --> 00:38:33,203
and I don't mean
to interfere.

552
00:38:33,244 --> 00:38:36,042
But why don't you take
it easy on the boy?

553
00:38:36,080 --> 00:38:38,446
I know you lost
your little girl.

554
00:38:38,482 --> 00:38:40,006
I lost my husband.

555
00:38:40,051 --> 00:38:42,178
It's been a tough day
on everyone.

556
00:38:42,219 --> 00:38:43,652
Tough day.

557
00:38:49,560 --> 00:38:51,118
Listen.

558
00:38:51,162 --> 00:38:52,720
Maybe it's help.

559
00:38:52,763 --> 00:38:54,663
No. It's Collie.

560
00:38:54,699 --> 00:38:56,860
I recognize the engine.

561
00:38:56,901 --> 00:39:00,564
His name is
Collie Entragian.

562
00:39:02,273 --> 00:39:04,241
He's been on the force
here for...

563
00:39:04,275 --> 00:39:07,574
about 12 years.

564
00:39:07,611 --> 00:39:09,875
I'm... I'm the vet
in these parts...

565
00:39:09,914 --> 00:39:13,213
and I took care of
Collie's dogs.

566
00:39:13,250 --> 00:39:15,241
He was a nice fellow.

567
00:39:15,286 --> 00:39:16,583
Yeah, a real sweetheart.

568
00:39:16,620 --> 00:39:18,588
Till this, I mean.

569
00:39:18,622 --> 00:39:20,920
I'll tell you
something, though.

570
00:39:23,394 --> 00:39:24,793
He's bigger.

571
00:39:24,829 --> 00:39:26,456
What do you mean,
"he's bigger"?

572
00:39:26,497 --> 00:39:27,464
Bigger.

573
00:39:27,498 --> 00:39:29,227
Taller.

574
00:39:29,266 --> 00:39:31,632
A few inches at least.

575
00:39:31,669 --> 00:39:33,762
That's impossible.

576
00:39:33,804 --> 00:39:36,295
I know.

577
00:39:44,382 --> 00:39:45,974
Look at us, would you.

578
00:39:46,016 --> 00:39:48,143
Just one big happy family.

579
00:39:48,185 --> 00:39:50,153
Tak.

580
00:40:01,899 --> 00:40:04,299
I don't even know
what I'm looking for.

581
00:40:04,335 --> 00:40:05,632
His bike...

582
00:40:05,669 --> 00:40:09,571
Skid marks, or just anything
out of the ordinary.

583
00:40:09,607 --> 00:40:12,940
- Wait, wait... what is that?
- What?

584
00:40:12,977 --> 00:40:15,878
He said something about an R.V.

585
00:40:15,913 --> 00:40:17,574
Hey!

586
00:40:17,615 --> 00:40:19,048
What? What is it?

587
00:40:20,050 --> 00:40:22,245
Just a reflection,
I guess. Go slow.

588
00:40:52,950 --> 00:40:54,315
Hello?

589
00:40:56,053 --> 00:40:57,418
Anybody home?

590
00:40:58,923 --> 00:41:00,015
Look.

591
00:41:01,325 --> 00:41:02,792
This is some little
girl's favorite.

592
00:41:02,827 --> 00:41:04,886
See how the dress
is patched?

593
00:41:04,929 --> 00:41:06,760
So why was it left
in the sand?

594
00:41:10,968 --> 00:41:12,299
Yeah. And why...

595
00:41:14,605 --> 00:41:16,971
Why are all the tires flat, you know?

596
00:41:17,007 --> 00:41:20,067
Like, not just one or two
of them, but all of them.

597
00:41:57,314 --> 00:41:59,077
Eeny, meeny, miney, mo.

598
00:42:03,220 --> 00:42:05,745
Catch a tourist by the toe.

599
00:42:16,166 --> 00:42:18,225
Don't you scream.

600
00:42:18,269 --> 00:42:19,702
Don't you shout.

601
00:42:23,040 --> 00:42:24,974
Time has come

602
00:42:25,009 --> 00:42:29,537
to take you... out.

603
00:42:29,580 --> 00:42:30,638
Leave them alone!

604
00:42:32,416 --> 00:42:33,383
Haven't you done
enough to us?

605
00:42:33,417 --> 00:42:34,884
In a word...

606
00:42:34,919 --> 00:42:35,886
No.

607
00:42:35,920 --> 00:42:38,718
Come on out, hon.

608
00:42:38,756 --> 00:42:41,816
Or this no chin,
pencil neck, paper pusher...

609
00:42:41,859 --> 00:42:43,850
gets it right
between the eyes.

610
00:42:48,098 --> 00:42:49,326
Ellie, no.

611
00:42:49,366 --> 00:42:50,697
And the boy goes next.

612
00:42:57,041 --> 00:42:58,531
No!

613
00:43:01,278 --> 00:43:02,905
I'll be all right.

614
00:43:02,947 --> 00:43:04,676
OK.

615
00:43:05,683 --> 00:43:08,618
That's right, hon.

616
00:43:08,652 --> 00:43:10,415
Fine as fiddlesticks.

617
00:43:14,558 --> 00:43:17,891
If you want that...

618
00:43:17,928 --> 00:43:19,759
take me where my son
won't have to see.

619
00:43:19,797 --> 00:43:21,162
Oh, don't worry, hon.

620
00:43:21,198 --> 00:43:23,689
I don't want "that. "

621
00:43:23,734 --> 00:43:26,396
Especially not from "you. "

622
00:43:28,105 --> 00:43:29,504
Mom, no!

623
00:43:29,540 --> 00:43:30,598
Leave her alone,
you bastard!

624
00:43:30,641 --> 00:43:31,938
Leave my mother alone.

625
00:43:31,976 --> 00:43:34,069
Don't worry, honey.
I'll be back. OK?

626
00:43:36,413 --> 00:43:38,108
Make him stop.
Dad, make him stop.

627
00:43:38,148 --> 00:43:40,116
Oh, God.

628
00:43:41,952 --> 00:43:44,785
I'm warning you.

629
00:43:44,822 --> 00:43:47,052
If you hurt her, you'll be sorry.

630
00:43:47,091 --> 00:43:49,389
Maybe.

631
00:43:49,426 --> 00:43:51,018
But I doubt it.

632
00:43:52,663 --> 00:43:55,461
You're just a little
prayboy, aren't you?

633
00:43:55,499 --> 00:43:57,558
Yes, yes, you are.

634
00:43:57,601 --> 00:44:01,560
You just little prayboy
in a baseball shirt.

635
00:44:01,605 --> 00:44:04,733
Well, go ahead and pray.

636
00:44:04,775 --> 00:44:06,504
See what good it does.

637
00:44:06,543 --> 00:44:09,512
But God ain't here
any more than he was...

638
00:44:09,546 --> 00:44:13,448
when Jesus was dying
on the cross with flies in his eyes.

639
00:44:13,484 --> 00:44:14,473
Tak!

640
00:44:18,889 --> 00:44:20,652
Tak! Ah lah!

641
00:44:22,326 --> 00:44:24,920
Him en tow!

642
00:44:28,866 --> 00:44:31,096
If you set a hand
or a foot outside your cell...

643
00:44:31,135 --> 00:44:33,126
he'll have it off before you
even know it was gone.

644
00:44:33,170 --> 00:44:34,228
Leave her alone.

645
00:44:34,271 --> 00:44:35,966
Son!

646
00:44:36,006 --> 00:44:38,566
I will put a stick through
your mother and spin her...

647
00:44:38,609 --> 00:44:41,578
until she catches fire
if I so desire.

648
00:44:41,612 --> 00:44:43,011
And you'll not stop me.

649
00:44:44,515 --> 00:44:46,005
And I'll come back for you.

650
00:44:49,053 --> 00:44:50,315
Collie!

651
00:44:52,823 --> 00:44:53,983
Don't hurt her!

652
00:45:02,599 --> 00:45:04,760
Carver. Carver.

653
00:45:23,687 --> 00:45:26,713
Well, there was boy here
as well as a girl.

654
00:45:26,757 --> 00:45:30,818
David Carver. Carver.

655
00:45:30,861 --> 00:45:32,692
What do you got?

656
00:45:32,730 --> 00:45:33,856
Jewelry.

657
00:45:33,897 --> 00:45:35,296
Earrings and rings.

658
00:45:35,332 --> 00:45:37,857
You know, not Tiffany,
but not cheap either.

659
00:45:37,901 --> 00:45:39,198
Not the kind of stuff
you'd leave behind...

660
00:45:39,236 --> 00:45:41,329
unless you were in a hurry.

661
00:45:44,641 --> 00:45:46,131
Time for the cops, isn't it?

662
00:45:46,176 --> 00:45:48,144
Well, I'm pretty sure
the boss said something...

663
00:45:48,178 --> 00:45:49,941
about being like
a mile from the R.V.

664
00:45:49,980 --> 00:45:52,039
So...

665
00:45:52,082 --> 00:45:54,050
Before we start
yelling for the cops...

666
00:46:20,377 --> 00:46:21,605
You're crazy.

667
00:47:01,251 --> 00:47:02,775
Cynthia!

668
00:47:56,473 --> 00:47:59,169
Why are you
taking me here?!

669
00:48:10,554 --> 00:48:13,216
It's beautiful, isn't it?

670
00:48:30,674 --> 00:48:32,403
Oh, God.

671
00:48:32,442 --> 00:48:33,807
Please, don't kill me.

672
00:48:35,679 --> 00:48:36,839
Just...

673
00:48:51,595 --> 00:48:53,927
Now what?

674
00:48:53,964 --> 00:48:56,262
Well, there's a town
not too far far east of here...

675
00:48:56,300 --> 00:48:58,131
Desperation.

676
00:48:58,168 --> 00:48:59,692
They got some cute names
out here, don't they?

677
00:48:59,736 --> 00:49:01,533
Yeah, I don't
care about the name.

678
00:49:01,571 --> 00:49:03,835
I just care about if they have
at least one working phone...

679
00:49:03,874 --> 00:49:06,206
and maybe
one working cop.

680
00:49:06,243 --> 00:49:08,438
Yeah.
Wouldn't that be nice.

681
00:49:38,742 --> 00:49:40,607
## Mother Mary ##

682
00:49:40,644 --> 00:49:42,202
## What's the story ##

683
00:49:42,245 --> 00:49:45,578
## Save my soul
from Purgatory ##

684
00:49:58,695 --> 00:49:59,787
Pie.

685
00:50:02,599 --> 00:50:04,430
Murder God.

686
00:50:04,468 --> 00:50:06,766
That's what it really says.

687
00:50:12,109 --> 00:50:15,943
Pie, I'm sorry
he killed you.

688
00:50:15,979 --> 00:50:17,810
Never mind.

689
00:50:17,848 --> 00:50:19,611
I have something for you.

690
00:50:21,785 --> 00:50:23,013
Tak ah lah!

691
00:50:23,053 --> 00:50:25,453
Tak!

692
00:50:29,793 --> 00:50:31,522
Look, David.

693
00:50:46,977 --> 00:50:48,535
David, are you OK?

694
00:50:51,715 --> 00:50:53,512
Could you
please turn around?

695
00:50:53,550 --> 00:50:54,983
This is a little
embarrassing.

696
00:50:57,854 --> 00:50:59,822
David, whatever
you have in mind...

697
00:50:59,856 --> 00:51:02,051
It can't be a good idea.

698
00:51:02,092 --> 00:51:03,081
It's the only idea.

699
00:51:03,126 --> 00:51:04,423
Who says so, son?

700
00:51:04,461 --> 00:51:06,622
My sister...

701
00:51:06,663 --> 00:51:07,652
God.

702
00:51:11,835 --> 00:51:12,859
Are you going to stop this...

703
00:51:12,903 --> 00:51:15,701
before you son does
something he regrets?

704
00:51:15,739 --> 00:51:17,036
David, you don't
have to do this.

705
00:51:17,074 --> 00:51:19,474
The cop's bleeding out.
He can't last much longer.

706
00:51:19,509 --> 00:51:20,908
It won't take him long...

707
00:51:20,944 --> 00:51:23,344
to kill my mom
if decides to.

708
00:51:23,380 --> 00:51:26,543
David, I don't know
what you're planning...

709
00:51:26,583 --> 00:51:28,210
But I forbid it.

710
00:51:28,251 --> 00:51:29,377
Sorry, Dad.

711
00:51:32,923 --> 00:51:33,912
What's he doing?

712
00:51:45,402 --> 00:51:48,098
David! David,
you don't have to do this.

713
00:51:48,138 --> 00:51:49,730
You'll get stuck.

714
00:51:52,075 --> 00:51:53,269
Even if you do get out,

715
00:51:53,310 --> 00:51:55,039
That thing'll eat you
from the feet up.

716
00:51:55,078 --> 00:51:58,241
Lord, close its mouth
like you did with the lions...

717
00:51:58,281 --> 00:52:00,841
When Daniel was cast
into their den.

718
00:52:02,652 --> 00:52:04,085
Amen.

719
00:52:06,556 --> 00:52:08,387
Stop it!

720
00:52:08,425 --> 00:52:10,723
Get away from him
you ugly bastard.

721
00:52:12,295 --> 00:52:13,284
Here, here. Here! Here!

722
00:52:13,330 --> 00:52:14,388
Hey! Hey, come on!

723
00:52:14,431 --> 00:52:15,557
Get over here,
you mutt.

724
00:52:19,136 --> 00:52:20,728
Come to me!
Come to me!

725
00:52:23,440 --> 00:52:25,203
Come on,
take another bite!

726
00:52:28,111 --> 00:52:29,373
Come this way!
Come to me!

727
00:52:37,621 --> 00:52:39,714
David, there's no time!
Come on, move!

728
00:52:40,857 --> 00:52:42,757
Get out of there, David!

729
00:52:42,792 --> 00:52:45,260
David, pull it!
Get out of there!

730
00:52:48,198 --> 00:52:49,756
Come on, come on!

731
00:52:52,936 --> 00:52:54,927
David, push!

732
00:52:59,676 --> 00:53:01,007
Get out!
Get out!

733
00:53:03,380 --> 00:53:04,938
Call the police!

734
00:53:04,981 --> 00:53:07,677
Run, run, David!

735
00:53:27,037 --> 00:53:29,232
Please help me
take care of my mom...

736
00:53:29,272 --> 00:53:31,604
and do what
I'm supposed to do.

737
00:54:23,560 --> 00:54:25,460
Hello?

738
00:54:26,663 --> 00:54:28,358
Anybody home?

739
00:54:37,240 --> 00:54:38,468
Tasteful.

740
00:54:38,508 --> 00:54:41,170
Operators are standing by.

741
00:54:41,211 --> 00:54:43,008
Hello?! Anybody there?

742
00:54:43,046 --> 00:54:44,707
It's dead!

743
00:54:44,748 --> 00:54:45,715
It's got to be the...

744
00:54:46,783 --> 00:54:48,080
Hey, wait! Wait! Wait!

745
00:54:48,118 --> 00:54:49,483
Wait.

746
00:54:49,519 --> 00:54:53,216
There are some garbage cans
lined up against the wall.

747
00:54:53,256 --> 00:54:54,951
The wind just knocked
one down. That's all.

748
00:54:54,991 --> 00:54:56,356
I don't care.
I want to get out of here.

749
00:54:56,393 --> 00:54:58,827
This place is empty,
and it gives me the creeps.

750
00:54:58,862 --> 00:55:01,126
There's trucks out there.

751
00:55:01,164 --> 00:55:03,098
Where is everybody?

752
00:55:03,133 --> 00:55:04,532
I don't know.
But I just think...

753
00:55:04,567 --> 00:55:05,898
we ought to just keep...

754
00:55:05,935 --> 00:55:06,993
I know, just tell me...

755
00:55:07,037 --> 00:55:08,368
we're going to be
laughing at each other...

756
00:55:08,405 --> 00:55:10,339
and feeling stupid
in a few seconds. OK?

757
00:55:10,373 --> 00:55:13,001
OK. A few seconds.

758
00:55:13,043 --> 00:55:14,874
Good enough.

759
00:55:14,911 --> 00:55:17,141
Let's see what we see.

760
00:55:18,815 --> 00:55:21,215
Do you hear that?

761
00:55:21,251 --> 00:55:23,776
Sounds like a kid blowing
bubbles through a straw.

762
00:55:25,488 --> 00:55:27,479
Do not worry, Little Nell,

763
00:55:27,524 --> 00:55:29,651
for I shall save you.

764
00:55:30,660 --> 00:55:31,854
Dork.

765
00:55:31,895 --> 00:55:33,829
Yeah.

766
00:55:45,375 --> 00:55:47,240
It's just an aquarium.

767
00:55:53,550 --> 00:55:54,710
No, look.

768
00:55:56,152 --> 00:55:57,414
Look.

769
00:55:57,454 --> 00:55:58,614
What?

770
00:56:01,891 --> 00:56:03,483
Behind the boat.

